    An enumeration of inference metrics that are commonly used.

      TOTAL_TIME
      The number of elapsed seconds used by the inference so far.
      WASTED_TIME_AFTER_LAST_ANSWER
      The number of elapsed seconds between when the last answer was found and the end of the inference.

        public static final StandardInferenceMetric TOTAL_TIME
        The number of elapsed seconds used by the inference so far. This does not include time spent preparing the inference, e.g. canonicalization, wff-checking, and setting up any hypothetical context.

      • WASTED_TIME_AFTER_LAST_ANSWER

        public static final StandardInferenceMetric WASTED_TIME_AFTER_LAST_ANSWER
        The number of elapsed seconds between when the last answer was found and the end of the inference. Equivalent to total time minus time to last answer.
